	</div>
	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64437388"><p>Ignoring the usual systemd hate / anti-Poettering rants... there's a lot of technical merit in this proposal.

</p><p>Writing secure SUID programs is <em>really, really hard.</em>.  And <tt>sudo</tt> is a very complicated piece of software with a huge attack surface.

</p><p>Having privileged programs started from a daemon with a controlled environment <em>that an attacker cannot manipulate</em> is a very good idea.  There's a good technical discussion of the merits over at <a href="https://lwn.net/Articles/971745/" title="lwn.net">LWN</a> [lwn.net].</p></div>
	</div>

	<div class="commentSub" id="comment_sub_64437388">

</div>
</div>

